'''Bowers Canyon''' ({{Coord|71|55|S|172|30|E|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is an undersea canyon west of [[Iselin Bank]] in the [[Ross Sea]]. It was named in association with [[Bowers Glacier]] by the [[Advisory Committee for Undersea Features]] in April 1980.

