'''Bret Wallach''' is an American cultural [[geographer]], and professor at [[University of Oklahoma]].<ref>http://ags.ou.edu/~bwallach/</ref>
He graduated from [[University of California, Berkeley]] with an A.B. in 1964, M.A. in 1966, and Ph.D. in 1968.<ref name="Berkeley">{{citation |url=http://core.geog.berkeley.edu/PeopleHistory/History/60YrsGeog/Wallach,%20Bret.html |title=Bret Wallach |publisher=University of California, Berkeley |accessdate=09-08-2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120422155626/http://core.geog.berkeley.edu/PeopleHistory/History/60YrsGeog/Wallach%2C%20Bret.html |archivedate=2012-04-22 |df= }}</ref> He taught at the [[University of Victoria]], [[Pennsylvania State University]], [[University of California, Riverside]], and [[University of Maine at Fort Kent]].
==Awards== * 1984 [[MacArthur Fellows Program]]
==Works== *[https://books.google.com/books?id=Q2J3YXhZaG8C&printsec=frontcover&dq=Bret+Wallach&hl=en&ei=0kuyS-Jfg7vyBtDkmNoB&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDoQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=&f=false ''Understanding the Cultural Landscape'']. New York: the Guilford Press, 2004. {{ISBN|978-1-59385-119-4}} *''Losing Asia: Modernization and the Culture of Development'', Baltimore and London: The Johns Hopkins Press, 1996. {{ISBN|978-0-8018-5170-4}} *''At Odds with Progress: Americans and Conservation''. Tucson: University of Arizona Press, 1991. {{ISBN|978-0-8165-0917-1}}
