[[File:Diplomatic missions in Niue.svg|thumb|450px|Map of diplomatic missions in Niue {{legend|#ff0000|Niue}} {{legend|#212178|States with embassy in Niue}} {{legend|#aaccff|States with non-resident embassy to Niue}}]]
This is a '''list of diplomatic missions in [[Niue]]''', a small Pacific island country in Oceania. Although Niue is an [[associated state]] of [[New Zealand]], {{Numrel|Niue|alt2=it maintains |diplomatic relations with|states|O=Y}}. At present, the capital of [[Alofi]] hosts one mission. Additionally there are embassies accredited to Niue and residing outside the country.{{#tag:ref|There is also non-resident delegation of [[European Union]] to Niue, based in [[Suva]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ec.europa.eu/external_relations/repdel/edelhrm/index.cfm |title=Accreditation and responsibilities | publisher=European External Action Service of the EU |date= |accessdate=2015-01-04}}</ref>|group="note"}}
==Embassies== Alofi {| | *{{NZL}} |}
==Non-resident embassies== {| | * {{AUS}} ([[Wellington]])<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfat.gov.au/geo/niue/niue_brief.html |title=Niue country brief| publisher=[[Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade (Australia)|Australian Government, Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade]]| year=2014 |accessdate=2014-08-03}}</ref> *{{flag|China}} (Wellington)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-10/18/content_10215471.htm |title=China's first ambassador to Niue presents credential to Niue PM |agency=[[Xinhua News Agency]] |date=2008-10-18 |accessdate=2015-01-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131116105311/http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-10/18/content_10215471.htm |archivedate=2013-11-16 |df= }}</ref> * {{FJI}} ([[Suva]])<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.pina.com.fj/?p=pacnews&m=read&o=1734056049563bdbca55aa29d69852 |title=Fijian community in Niue host Fijian delegates attending Pacific Community Conference | publisher=Pacific Islands News Association | date=2015-11-05 |accessdate=2016-01-30 |quote=Cabinet has approved Fiji’s Roving Ambassador Litia Mawi as Ambassador to Niue and we look forward to her presenting her credentials to Cabinet.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foreignaffairs.gov.fj/head-quarters/roving-ambassador |title=Roving Ambassador | publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Fiji | date= |accessdate=2016-01-30 |quote=Roving Ambassador/High Commissioner...based in Suva...Accredited to...Niue}}</ref> * {{FRA}} (Wellington)<ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.ambafrance-nz.org/Ambassador-of-France-H-E-M-Laurent |title = Ambassador Contini presents his credentials in Samoa |publisher = Embassy of France in Wellington |date = 2014-10-04 |accessdate = 2015-01-04 |deadurl = yes |archiveurl = https://archive.is/20150104215716/http://www.ambafrance-nz.org/Ambassador-of-France-H-E-M-Laurent |archivedate = 2015-01-04 |df = }} "Ambassador of France... is also accredited to... Niue."</ref> * {{IND}} (Wellington)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mea.gov.in/press-releases.htm?dtl/23563/Ravi+Thapar+concurrently+accredited+as+the+next+High+Commissioner+of+India+to+Niue |title=Ravi Thapar concurrently accredited as the next High Commissioner of India to Niue |publisher=Ministry of Foreign Affairs of India |date=2014-07-07 |accessdate=2015-01-04}}</ref>{{#tag:ref|India is the only state that has accredited different embassies to Niue and to the [[Cook Islands]] (Indian embassy to the Cook Islands is based in Suva).<ref>{{Cite web |title=Shri Vinod Kumar concurrently accredited as the High Commissioner of India to Nauru and Cook Islands |url=http://mea.gov.in/press-releases.htm?dtl/664/Shri+Vinod+Kumar+concurrently+accredited+as+the+High+Commissioner+of+India+to+Nauru+and+Cook+Islands |publisher=Ministry of External Affairs of India |date=2011-03-09 |accessdate=2016-01-28}}</ref>|group="note"}} * {{ISR}} (Wellington)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mfa.gov.il/MFA/AboutTheMinistry/Pages/Israel-s%20Diplomatic%20Missions%20Abroad.aspx#note|title=Israel's Diplomatic Missions Abroad: Status of relations |publisher=[[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Israel)|Israeli Ministry of Foreign Affairs]]|date= |accessdate=2014-07-28}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mic.gov.to/state-visits/4237-israeli-ambassador-to-tonga-he-shemi-tzur-visited-tonga |title=Israeli Ambassador to Tonga HE Shemi Tzur visited Tonga |publisher=Ministry of Information and Communications of Tonga|date=2013-02-04 |accessdate=2014-07-28}} "Israeli Ambassador... is also accredited to... Niue."</ref> *{{JPN}} (Wellington)<ref>{{Cite web |title=Embassy of Japan in Niue |url=http://www.nz.emb-japan.go.jp/jointad/nu/en/index.html |publisher=Embassy of Japan in New Zealand |date= |accessdate=2016-01-27}}</ref> * {{MYS}} (Wellington) * {{PNG}} (Wellington) |}
