The '''list of hoards in Asia''' comprises significant [[Archaeology|archaeological]] [[hoard]]s of coins, jewellery, precious and scrap metal objects and other valuable items discovered in [[Asia]]. It includes both hoards that were buried with the intention of retrieval at a later date (personal hoards, [[Foundry|founder's]] hoards, merchant's hoards, and hoards of loot), and also hoards of [[votive offering]]s which were not intended to be recovered at a later date, but excludes [[grave goods]] and single items found in isolation.

*[[Bactrian Gold]]
*[[Chausa hoard]]
*[[Kfar Monash Hoard]]
*[[Wonoboyo hoard]]
*[[Ziwiye hoard]]

