{{Unreferenced|date=April 2015}} {{Infobox settlement | name = Meneng | settlement_type = [[Districts of Nauru|District]] | image_skyline = | imagesize = 250px | image_caption = | image_flag = | image_shield = | nickname = | motto = | image_map = Meneng in Nauru.svg | mapsize = | map_caption = Meneng District within Nauru | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{NRU}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Constituencies of Nauru|Constituency]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Meneng Constituency|Meneng]] | established_title = | established_date = | established_title1 = <!--City rights--> | established_date1 = | leader_title = | leader_name = | area_magnitude = | area_total_km2 = 3.1 | area_land_km2 = | area_water_km2 = | population_as_of = 2011 | population_note = | population_total = 1,380 | population_footnotes = | population_metro = | population_density_km2 = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_map1 = | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_map_caption1 = | pushpin_mapsize = | coordinates = {{coord|0|32|53|S|166|56|22|E|display=inline,title}} | timezone = ([[UTC+12:00|UTC+12]]) | utc_offset = | elevation_m = 25 | postal_code_type = [[Postal code]]| | postal_code = | area_code = [[Telephone numbers in Nauru|+674]] | blank_info = | blank1_info = | website = | footnotes = }} '''Meneng''' (or '''Menen''') is a [[district]] located in the [[Meneng Constituency]] in the country of [[Nauru]]. The constituency elects 2 members to the [[Parliament of Nauru]] in [[Yaren District|Yaren]].
==Geography== The district is located in the southeast of the island, covering an area of 3.1&nbsp;km². It has a population of 1,400. Meneng District has 18 villages, the most of any district in Nauru.
==Local features== Features in Meneng include:
* The [[Menen Hotel]], one of the island's two hotels * the wireless station * the State House (presidential residence; recently burned down) * the Government Printing Office * the [[Meneng Stadium]] * Australian [[Nauru Detention Centre]]
==Education== {{seealso|Education in Nauru}} Meneng Infant School is in Meneng.<ref name=EdStats2015>"[https://prism.spc.int/component/advlisting/?view=download&format=raw&fileId=85 Education Statistics Digest 2015]." [[Department of Education (Nauru)]]. Retrieved on July 8, 2018. p. 47 (PDF p. 47).</ref> The primary and secondary schools serving all of Nauru are Yaren Primary School in [[Yaren District]] (years 1-3), Nauru Primary School in Meneng District (years 4-6), Nauru College in [[Denigomodu District]] (years 7-9), and [[Nauru Secondary School]] (years 10-12) in Yaren District.<ref name=OHCHR>[http://docstore.ohchr.org/SelfServices/FilesHandler.ashx?enc=6QkG1d/PPRiCAqhKb7yhsqMFgv33OTgoZv7ZAgL6thBs%2BJaDouDrmbrhkSKQnAJmPZ9UvJeFASCaHOYMWlSYYCuENbqZ7%2B4S5kzfEKujpCmbACo3%2BCb5LwxaXyHF2qjW Document by the]." [[OHCHR]]. Retrieved on 8 July 2018. "The Education system is {{sic|comprised |hide=y|of}} 10 schools, there are District Infant schools each[...]and finally Nauru Secondary School (Years 10-12) where compulsory education end at Year 12.[...]"</ref>
The current building of Nauru Primary School opened on October 6, 2016. Canstruct, an Australian firm, built the two story building, which has eight classrooms. The building, specially designed for Nauruan weather, with ceiling fans and special airflow, may house up to 400 students and is resistant to natural disasters.<ref>"[http://nauru-news.com/new-nauru-primary-school-adds-to-high-class-education-system/ New Nauru Primary School adds to high class education system]." Government of Nauru. Retrieved on June 5, 2018.</ref>
