{{Infobox settlement |official_name =Miruşen |native_name = |pushpin_map =Azerbaijan |pushpin_mapsize =300 |subdivision_type = Country |subdivision_name = {{flag|Azerbaijan}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Administrative divisions of Azerbaijan|Rayon]] |subdivision_name1 =[[Khojavend Rayon|Khojavend]] |leader_title = |leader_name = |established_title = |established_date = |area_total_km2 = |area_footnotes = |population_as_of = |population_total = |population_density_km2 = |timezone =[[Azerbaijan Time|AZT]] |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST =[[Azerbaijan Time|AZT]] |utc_offset_DST = +5 |coordinates = {{coord|39|50|33|N|46|55|10|E|region:AZ|display=inline}} |elevation_m = |area_code = |website = }} '''Miruşen''' ({{lang-hy|Միրուշեն}}) (also, '''Mirikend''', '''Mirikənd''', '''Mirishen''', '''Mirushen''', and '''Myurishen''') is a village in the [[Martuni Province]] of the de facto [[Republic of Artsakh]], de jure part of the Republic of Azerbaijan.
